{"type":"text","timestamp":1773436128040,"sessionID":"ses_316fcbbc9ffe0U7d2IN0Q9PcrR","part":{"id":"prt_ce9075865001XcWIBx3u0WI3s1","sessionID":"ses_316fcbbc9ffe0U7d2IN0Q9PcrR","messageID":"msg_ce9074ea6001pTvmKItoSc5Xbv","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a TOON (Token-Optimized Output Notation) output formatter module for the wombo-combo CLI tool. TOON is a compact, pipe-delimited format designed for AI agent consumption that reduces token count by 60%+ vs JSON. The module needs to handle all data types: task lists, status dashboards, wave state, verification results, and history.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Create `src/lib/toon.ts` with per-command renderers for tasks list, tasks show, status, verify, history, and tasks check\n- Integrate with existing `OutputFormat = \"text\" | \"json\" | \"toon\"` in `src/lib/output.ts` by adding a toon rendering path to the `output()` function\n- Status codes: BL=backlog, PL=planned, IP=in_progress, BK=blocked, IR=in_review, DN=done, CN=cancelled\n- Priority codes: C=critical, H=high, M=medium, L=low, W=wishlist\n- Difficulty codes: T=trivial, E=easy, M=medium, H=hard, V=very_hard\n- Use conventional commits scoped to `toon-output-formatter`\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `undefined`\n- Run `bun run build` to verify before considering task complete\n- Branch: `feature/toon-output-formatter`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` already existed with all the encoding/decoding mappings (status codes, priority codes, difficulty codes, duration encoding, boolean encoding, array encoding) and command field specifications. The new `toon.ts` module imports from it.\n- `OutputFormat` type already included `\"toon\"` and `resolveOutputFormat()` already handled `\"toon\"` - these were pre-existing.\n- The `output()` function signature was `output(format, data, textRenderer)` — updated to `output(format, data, textRenderer, toonRenderer?)` with optional 4th parameter for TOON-specific rendering.\n- The `describe` command in `index.ts` already had TOON format handling via `renderToonLegend()` and `buildToonSpec()`.\n- TypeScript typecheck passes cleanly after all changes.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed:\n1. **Created `src/lib/toon.ts`** — Core TOON formatter module with renderers:\n   - `renderTasksList()` — pipe-delimited task list with #FIELDS header\n   - `renderTaskShow()` — key:value pairs with abbreviated keys (id, st, pr, df, ef, cp, dm, dp, sa, ea, ti, ds, cn, fb, rf, nt, sc)\n   - `renderStatus()` — wave status with #WAVE summary + per-agent lines\n   - `renderVerify()` — feature_id|pass_fail|duration\n   - `renderHistoryList()` — wave history list\n   - `renderHistoryDetail()` — single wave detail with per-agent breakdown\n   - `renderTasksCheck()` — check results with #CHECK summary\n   - `renderGeneric()` — fallback for data without specific formatters\n\n2. **Updated `src/lib/output.ts`** — Added TOON paths:\n   - `output()` now accepts optional `toonRenderer` callback (4th param), falls back to `renderGeneric()` \n   - `outputError()` emits `#ERROR message` in TOON mode\n   - `outputMessage()` emits `#MSG message` in TOON mode\n\n3. **Updated command files** to pass TOON renderers to `output()`:\n   - `src/commands/tasks/list.ts` — uses `renderTasksList()`\n   - `src/commands/tasks/show.ts` — uses `renderTaskShow()`\n   - `src/commands/status.ts` — uses `renderStatus()`\n   - `src/commands/history.ts` — uses `renderHistoryList()` and `renderHistoryDetail()`\n   - `src/commands/tasks/check.ts` — uses `renderTasksCheck()`\n\n4. **TypeScript typecheck passes** (`bun run typecheck` — clean)\n5. **One commit made**: `feat(toon-output-formatter): add TOON formatter module and update output helpers` (commit 0da435b)\n\n### Still needed:\n- **Commit the command file changes** (list.ts, show.ts, status.ts, history.ts, check.ts are modified but not committed)\n- **Run `bun run build`** to verify the build passes\n- Fix any build errors if they occur\n- Commands like `abort.ts`, `logs.ts`, `graph.ts` use `output()` without specific TOON renderers — they'll use the generic fallback, which is fine\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n- **Created**: `src/lib/toon.ts` — Core TOON formatter module\n- **Modified**: `src/lib/output.ts` — Added TOON rendering path to output(), outputError(), outputMessage()\n- **Modified**: `src/commands/tasks/list.ts` — Added TOON renderer callback\n- **Modified**: `src/commands/tasks/show.ts` — Added TOON renderer callback\n- **Modified**: `src/commands/status.ts` — Added TOON renderer callback\n- **Modified**: `src/commands/history.ts` — Added TOON renderer callback\n- **Modified**: `src/commands/tasks/check.ts` — Added TOON renderer callback\n- **Read (reference)**: `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` — Pre-existing TOON spec with encode/decode mappings\n- **Read (reference)**: `src/lib/tasks.ts` — Task/Feature types (TaskStatus, Priority, Difficulty, Task)\n- **Read (reference)**: `src/lib/state.ts` — WaveState, AgentState types\n- **Read (reference)**: `src/lib/history.ts` — WaveHistoryRecord, AgentHistoryRecord types\n- **Read (reference)**: `src/index.ts` — CLI entry point, command routing\n- **Read (reference)**: `src/commands/abort.ts`, `src/commands/logs.ts`, `src/commands/tasks/graph.ts` — Use output() but rely on generic fallback\n- **Config**: `tsconfig.json`, `package.json`","time":{"start":1773436128039,"end":1773436128039}}}
